Basic
Keyword: Keywords are the reserved words of a language.
Identifier: Identifiers are the user-defined names of variables, functions, and labels.

Use
Keyword: Specify the type/kind of entity.
Identifier: Identify the name of a particular entity.

Format
Keyword: Consider only letters.
Identifier: Consider letters, underscores, and digits.

Case
Keyword: Use only lowercase.
Identifier: Lowercase and uppercase, both are allowed.

Symbol
Keyword: No special symbol or punctuation is used.
Identifier: No punctuation or special symbol except underscore is used.

Classifications
Keyword: Keyword not further classified.
Identifier: Identifiers are classified into external and internal names.

Starting Letter
Keyword: It always starts with a lowercase letter.
Identifier: First character can be uppercase, lowercase, or underscore.
